metadata.name: Dencity #980
metadata.description:
Dencity is a generative art project inspired by aerial views of cities with a high density of buildings. Its perspective effect, its perfectly imprecise lines, its subtle textures and its very advanced level of detail give it the appearance of a hand-drawn work.

Behind the visible art (the image) hides another form of art, an extremely complex algorithm capable of calculating and drawing in 2D each variation of the Dencity project. To draw a variation, the algorithm notably takes around 3,000,000 to 20,000,000 random decisions based on the hash of the mint and draws around 800,000 to 4,000,000 lines to create all the strokes and texture effects.

Made with ❤️, code and p5js.

metadata.name: Frost's Road #225
metadata.description:
Do you take the less traveled road and dispel the wonder of what might have been?  Or, do you preserve the mystery by gazing down the overgrown, winding path savoring the speculation--never to be disappointed or have your wonder sated?

Frost's Road celebrates the obvious and enigmatic themes of Frost's poem, "The Road Not Taken."  A generative path to nowhere? Or someplace special?  Frost's Road subtly captures the obviousness of a vacant path, and the questions that lingers about why is that.

Created with p5js.

Press the Down Arrow to save the frame as a png.
Click or tap the canvas to toggle full screen mode.
Output Size: 995 x 1080.

metadata.name: notturno generativo #103
metadata.description:
by fabiello.art

my first generative nft is a nocturnal landscape written in p5.js, where I present my personal fusion of code and figurative art, a vision of hills and trees under a sky of stars and a full moon.
Each iteration presents a number of random variables such as to make the possible night scenarios tend to infinity, each capable of evoking different emotions due to its colors and shapes.

I like to imagine how every possible landscape is somehow connected to a physical or metaphysical place of the personal experience of the beholder. 
The use of the machine and the code, of human thought and its evolution up to our time, as an instrument of discovery and imaginative exploration of territories of the body and the soul.

The code of the trees is derived from J. Poliachik's Generative Trees.
1080x1080 px 
_

https://twitter.com/fabielloart

metadata.name: Sunset in Paradise #157
metadata.description:
Hundreds of Walkers descend the screen drawing a sky, sea and the sun reflection; creating a twilight scene of a sunset or possibly a sunrise depending on which coast your paradise can be found. 
Features - 32 Palettes 
5 Possible background colors per palette
3 different complexities of sky:
	-Refined - 3 colors (25% chance)
	-Complex - 5 colors (25% chance)
	-Normal - 4 colors (50% chance)
2 possible border colors: 
	Matching the sun color (40% chance) 
	Matching the sea color (60% chance)
2 different stroke thickness: 
	Fine (25% chance) 
	Medium-point (75% chance) 
Different amounts of Walkers for Sky, Sea and reflection.

Made by @p1x3lboy in p5.js
June 2022

metadata.name: a fleeting moment #31
metadata.description:
Abstract expressionism always has been, and always will be, my first love. With this piece, the initial premise was "can I write a bit of code that will render images in the style that I actually paint in real life?" 

It took several full days of poking and prodding, and I departed from the original mission once I had what I was looking for, but in general, I think I succeeded. My wife was looking over my shoulder at one point, and thought I was looking at a scan of one of my actual paintings, which sounds like success to me. 

Created with love in p5.js

metadata.name: Morning Mist #118

metadata.description:
Penumbra is a geometric exploration of the possible outcomes from 3 basic rules:
